marinate chicken with red chili, salt, and garlic powder. 
in a pot of boiling water, add pasta and boil for 15 minutes 
cut the peppers and onions in small pieces then add in another pot, fry onions, 
salt, peppers, basil leaves, and oregano. after it is done frying, 
add in the pasta sauce, and thouroughly mix. strain the pasta and add it into the 
sauce mixture then let simmer for 5-10 mins. take out the marinated chicken and 
on a medium heated pan, let cook on all sides until golden brown.
after its done, either cut and keep it in the pasta, or eat seperately on one plate.
then ENJOY!
